<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,150,1217]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C." box="[354,616,151,177]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="233 - 316" refId="ref14237" refString="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C. (2004) Verzeichnis der Typen der Vogelsammlung des Museums fur Tierkunde in den Staatlichen Naturhistorischen Sammlungen Dresden. Zoologische Abhandlungen, Dresden, 54, 233 - 316." type="journal article" year="2004">Eck &amp; Quaisser (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, another specimen that was part of the 1930 exchange to USNM, C7596, was also a 
<typeStatus box="[274,361,186,212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">syntype</typeStatus>
(USNM 317784; 
<bibRefCitation author="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C." box="[565,811,185,211]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="233 - 316" refId="ref14237" refString="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C. (2004) Verzeichnis der Typen der Vogelsammlung des Museums fur Tierkunde in den Staatlichen Naturhistorischen Sammlungen Dresden. Zoologische Abhandlungen, Dresden, 54, 233 - 316." type="journal article" year="2004">Eck &amp; Quaisser 2004</bibRefCitation>
). There are, however, no indications in either the MTD/ SNSD or USNM catalogues, or on the labels currently on the specimen in the USNM collection, of it being a type (in the USNM catalogue 
<emphasis box="[438,529,255,281]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">‘cotype’</emphasis>
is noted for 317785, while for 317784 only 
<emphasis box="[1037,1191,255,281]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">‘new to mus.’</emphasis>
is noted; Christopher Milensky, pers. comm.). Further, only 317785 is mentioned in the USNM type catalogue by 
<bibRefCitation author="Deignan, H. G." box="[1186,1367,289,316]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="1 - 718" refId="ref13987" refString="Deignan, H. G. (1961) Type specimens of birds in the United States National Museum. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 221, 1 - 718. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.221" type="journal article" year="1961">Deignan (1961)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,150,1217]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">
On the other hand, a specimen in the AMNH should probably be added to the type series. 
<bibRefCitation author="Greenway, J. C. J." box="[1238,1436,324,350]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="1 - 306" refId="ref14606" refString="Greenway, J. C. J. (1978) Type specimens of birds in the American Museum of Natural History. Part 2. Otididae, Jacanidae, Rostratulidae, Haematopodidae, Charadriidae, Scolopacidae, Recurvirostridae, Burhinidae, Glareolidae, Thinocoridae, Stercorariidae, Laridae, Alcidae, Pteroclididae, Columbidae, Psittacidae, Musophagidae, Cuculidae, Tytonidae, Strigidae, Podargidae, Nyctibiidae, Aegothelidae, Caprimulgidae, Apodidae, Hemiprocnidae, Trochilidae, Coliidae, Trogonidae, Alcedinidae, Momotidae, Meropidae, Leptosomatidae, Coraciidae, Upupidae, Phoeniculidae, Bucerotidae, Galbulidae, Bucconidae, Capitonidae, Indicatoridae, Ramphastidae, Picidae. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 161 (1), 1 - 306." type="journal article" year="1978">Greenway (1978)</bibRefCitation>
listed specimen AMNH 620706, originating from the Rothschild collection at Tring, as a 
<typeStatus box="[1190,1296,359,385]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">lectotype</typeStatus>
, stating that 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert, E." box="[151,312,393,420]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="112 - 134" refId="ref14830" refString="Hartert, E. (1924) Types of birds in the Tring museum. B. Types in the general collection. IV. Novitates Zoologicae, 31, 112 - 134." type="journal article" year="1924">Hartert (1924)</bibRefCitation>
had designated this type. As also pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C." box="[857,1117,393,419]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="233 - 316" refId="ref14237" refString="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C. (2004) Verzeichnis der Typen der Vogelsammlung des Museums fur Tierkunde in den Staatlichen Naturhistorischen Sammlungen Dresden. Zoologische Abhandlungen, Dresden, 54, 233 - 316." type="journal article" year="2004">Eck &amp; Quaisser (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, this was a misinterpretation of 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert, E." box="[182,361,428,454]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="112 - 134" refId="ref14830" refString="Hartert, E. (1924) Types of birds in the Tring museum. B. Types in the general collection. IV. Novitates Zoologicae, 31, 112 - 134." type="journal article" year="1924">Hartert’s (1924)</bibRefCitation>
wording, as he referred to it as a 
<emphasis box="[738,830,428,454]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">‘cotype’</emphasis>
, but mentioned that Meyer had written 
<emphasis box="[1276,1359,428,454]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">‘Typus’</emphasis>
on the label. While there is no evidence supporting that Meyer designated any 
<typeStatus box="[958,1056,463,489]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">holotype</typeStatus>
among the 
<typeStatus box="[1188,1289,463,489]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">syntypes</typeStatus>
, the status of AMNH 620706 as a 
<emphasis box="[384,476,498,524]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">‘cotype’</emphasis>
, i.e. 
<typeStatus box="[531,621,498,524]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">syntype</typeStatus>
, as stated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert, E." box="[770,933,497,524]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="112 - 134" refId="ref14830" refString="Hartert, E. (1924) Types of birds in the Tring museum. B. Types in the general collection. IV. Novitates Zoologicae, 31, 112 - 134." type="journal article" year="1924">Hartert (1924)</bibRefCitation>
, seems to be warranted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,150,1217]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">
So far, it therefore seems plausible that AMNH 620706 represents an 11 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1033,1046,532,546]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">th</superScript>
<typeStatus box="[1055,1142,533,559]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">syntype</typeStatus>
of this taxon, rather than USNM 317784. The situation is, however, more complex, as there are in addition to the aforementioned specimens, also 
<specimenCount box="[203,369,601,628]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
each in NHMW and NHMO that apparently are 
<typeStatus box="[917,1015,602,628]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">syntypes</typeStatus>
of this taxon. The two in NHMW are both included in type catalogues from the collection (
<bibRefCitation author="Pelzeln, A. &amp; Lorenz, L." box="[761,1031,636,663]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="37 - 62" refId="ref15941" refString="Pelzeln, A. v. &amp; Lorenz, L. v. (1888) Typen der ornithologischen Sammlung des k. k. naturhistorischen Hofmuseums. IV. Theil (Schluss). Annalen des K. K. Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums, 3 (1), 37 - 62." type="journal article" year="1888">Pelzeln &amp; Lorenz 1888</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schifter, H. &amp; Bauernfeind, E. &amp; Schifter, T." box="[1045,1268,636,662]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="1 - 376" refId="ref16471" refString="Schifter, H., Bauernfeind, E. &amp; Schifter, T. (2007) Die Typen der Vogelsammlung des Naturhistorischen Museums Wien. Teil I. Nonpasseres. Kataloge der wissenschaftlichen Sammlungen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 20 (Aves, Heft 1), 1 - 376." type="journal article" year="2007">
Schifter 
<emphasis box="[1142,1200,636,662]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
), and although they are described as 
<emphasis box="[391,679,671,697]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">‘authentische Exemplare’</emphasis>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pelzeln, A. &amp; Lorenz, L." box="[719,1000,671,697]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="37 - 62" refId="ref15941" refString="Pelzeln, A. v. &amp; Lorenz, L. v. (1888) Typen der ornithologischen Sammlung des k. k. naturhistorischen Hofmuseums. IV. Theil (Schluss). Annalen des K. K. Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums, 3 (1), 37 - 62." type="journal article" year="1888">Pelzeln &amp; Lorenz (1888)</bibRefCitation>
, they are noted as 
<emphasis box="[1206,1272,671,697]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">‘type’</emphasis>
in the acquisition catalogue (Hans-Martin Berg, pers. comm.; see 
<bibRefCitation author="Schifter, H." box="[749,921,705,731]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="63 - 73" refId="ref16437" refString="Schifter, H. (1990) Dr. Adolf Bernhard Meyer und die Vogelsammlung des Naturhistorischen Museums Wien. Zoologische Abhandlungen, Dresden, 46 (3), 63 - 73." type="journal article" year="1990">Schifter (1990)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Schifter, H. &amp; Bauernfeind, E. &amp; Schifter, T." box="[979,1217,705,731]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="1 - 376" refId="ref16471" refString="Schifter, H., Bauernfeind, E. &amp; Schifter, T. (2007) Die Typen der Vogelsammlung des Naturhistorischen Museums Wien. Teil I. Nonpasseres. Kataloge der wissenschaftlichen Sammlungen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 20 (Aves, Heft 1), 1 - 376." type="journal article" year="2007">
Schifter 
<emphasis box="[1076,1134,705,731]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">et al.</emphasis>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
for a discussion of the term 
<emphasis box="[250,537,740,766]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">‘authentische Exemplare’</emphasis>
in NHMW). Regarding the two in NHMO, all available evidence in the NHMO, including original catalogue entries, the accompanying letter from Meyer and the labels, they both appear as valid, undebatable 
<typeStatus box="[293,395,810,836]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">syntypes</typeStatus>
. The letter, in Meyer’s original handwriting, clearly states that four of the specimens listed as included in the shipment (this pair of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1884" box="[576,859,844,870]" class="Aves" family="Psittacidae" genus="Geoffroyus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psittaciformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="timorlaoensis">
<emphasis box="[576,859,844,870]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
plus single specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Musschenbroeki" authorityName="Musschenbroeki Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1884" box="[1151,1436,844,870]" class="Aves" family="Artamidae" genus="Artamus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1151,1436,844,870]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">Artamus Musschenbroeki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1884" box="[201,463,879,905]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ptilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavovirescens">
<emphasis box="[201,463,879,905]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">Ptilopus flavovirescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are types (
<figureCitation box="[601,698,879,905]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-24@2.[191,1396,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Facsimile of parts of the letter from A. B. Meyer to R. Collett 11 July 1886, including the section about the content of the shipment sent to Oslo the same day, plus the header and signature parts." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626763" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626763/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">Figure 1</figureCitation>
). As shown in the entries for the two other taxa, there seems to be no reason to doubt the authenticity of the type status of those. It is also worth noting that the pair of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1882" class="Aves" family="Psittacidae" genus="Eclectus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psittaciformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="riedeli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">Eclectus riedeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
included in the shipment (see above) are 
<emphasis box="[702,738,949,974]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">not</emphasis>
indicated as types, lending credibility to the reliability of the information provided in the letter. No documentation of this exchange has, however, been found in the MTD/SNSD catalogues.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,150,1217]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="NHMO" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" specimenCount="11" typeStatus="syntype">
In conclusion, the number of alleged type specimens of this taxon exceed the 
<specimenCount box="[1089,1241,1052,1078]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" type="generic">11 specimens</specimenCount>
on which Meyer based his description. As there seem to be reliable information supporting the type status of most or all of these (perhaps except C7596), we recommend more detailed investigations of all specimens allegedly included in the type series before any solid conclusions are made. We therefore maintain the two 
<collectionCode box="[1013,1099,1156,1182]" country="Norway" name="Natural History Museum, University of Oslo" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" type="Museum">NHMO</collectionCode>
specimens as 
<typeStatus box="[1260,1358,1157,1183]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">syntypes</typeStatus>
of this taxon
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
